value.0: I welcome you into the ShadowGuard, my <brother/sister>...
Would you like some help in your mission?
As you wish.
Very good, <mister/missus> <LastName>
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 9. USING THIS FOR TESTING AT THE MOMENT! >>
Glad to have ya' aboard, <FirstName>. I'm sure you'll find the ShadowGuard just to your liking...
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_ST_2_MAIN" >>
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 2. >>
How 'bout speaking with the Overlord so we can get ourselves out of Ghaarak...
Let's get out of here, <FirstName>!
That wasn't so bad, I suppose... Why don't you speak with Markius, <lad/lass>?
Too much excitement for me for one day... I say we make our way out of Ghaarak...
I've got a bad feeling about this, <FirstName>...
How 'bout we get out of this place before it's too late, <FirstName>? I've got a bad feeling we won't last for long if we stay in Ghaarak...
<StartAction>[Tarin looks around nervously, but nods his head.]</Start> As you wish, <FirstName>. Just be sure to come get me... if you need my help...
The Market District isn't pretty at the moment, <CUSTOM6004>. You'd better talk with Markius...
<StartAction>[This little Halfling gives you an impish smile as you draw near.]</Start>
You lent me your aid against Nightcrawler's men, now let me give you mine! I have all manner of useful roguish skills, all of which I am willing to put at your disposal, <FirstName>!
Good to see you again, <FirstName>, though I regret that it has to be under such unfortunate circumstances...
Aye, at least for the time being anyway. You see, these fine chaps are helping me pay off some of my old gambling debts... They're fairly nice folk as well, once you get used to 'em...
Tarin Lightfingers, Halfling card player extraordinaire, at your service, and pleased to meet ya'!
Okay... Come back if you need me help...
Now, would you care for me to lend my roguish talents to you in making our way to the docks, and perhaps getting out of this dreadful place?
Lead the way, <FirstName>! You can count on Tarin Lightfingers to keep ya' out of trouble!
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_ST_1_MAIN" >>
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_PREL_TARI" >>
The Market District isn't pretty at the moment, <CUSTOM6004>. You'd better talk with Markius...
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_ST_1_MAIN" >>
<StartAction>[As you approach the diminutive form of Tarin Lightingers, he does not immediately take notice. Instead, his attention is drawn to a chest of gold lying before him...]</Start>
<StartAction>[Tarin jumps excitely, and spins towards you.]</Start> Oh... uh... aye, hello there, <FirstName>. You... you caught me a bit unawares, I'm afraid.
So, what can ol' Tarin do for you on this fine evening, <lad/lass>?
Aye, no worries, <FirstName>. Have yourself a good evening, and stop in anytime...

<StartAction>[Tarin's typically cheerful face turns a bit dour.]</Start> Ah... the Final Initiation... A true beast of a trial, it is, my <lad/lass>... one which you should prepare yourself well for...
'Tis difficult to say much on it, for the trial depends on the nature of the one taking it, but rest assured Rakha will test your ability to strike swiftly in stealth and subterfuge.
After all, we of the ShadowGuard must be prepared to act under the guise of deception if we are to be effective, and Rakha will want to ensure you are capable of acting with us.
Don't worry too much over it, though. Just keep your wits about you, and I'm sure you can handle anything the Emperor may throw at you...
<StartAction>[Tarin raises his eyebrow at you slyly.]</Start> Going prying about in others' affairs, eh? Can't say I blame you for wanting to know about your companions, so ask away!
Vhorkas keeps this whole organization running, he does. Without the Overlord, can't see as how we'd truly be effective. He takes the orders straight from Emperor Rakha and delivers them to us.
Vhorkas has been a good leader to us all, ensuring we have what we need to accomplish both his goals and our own. Do your duties well, and you can be assured Vhorkas will watch out for you...
Kara's a beautiful thing, 'tis sure, but she's got a fire in her eyes behind that sultry glint. Trust me, <lad/lass>. She can be just as dangerous as she is gorgeous...

But if you ask me, Kara's decent enough at heart. 'Tis just her dark past that haunts her, and that's one tale I won't tell in these halls. You'll have to talk with her more if you want the whole story on that one...
Markius? He's a decent enough sort, though he's a bit too strict with the letter of Rakha's law for my tastes. Still, he makes sure we're all kept safe and sound, so that gives him my good graces...
I have to say, Markius would die for any of us should it come to it, and he never falters in battle, no matter what the circumstance. You can put your trust in Markius, my <lad/lass>.
<StartAction>[Tarin looks at you suspiciously.]</Start> And why should I trust someone like you? You'd have left me to Pharos Nightcrawler's cronies in Ghaarak, after all...
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> Aye, I suppose you didn't know who I was then... and you do seem decent enough now. Very well, I guess I can trust you enough to tell the tale...
<StartAction>[Tarin opens his mouth as if to speak, but then seems to think otherwise.]</Start> I... I don't know, <FirstName>. I'm not sure I'm ready to trust you that much just yet...
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> I'm afraid I'm just not ready to trust you yet, <FirstName>... Come, let us speak of something else...
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> Oh, I suppose you're right, <FirstName>. After all, you are one of us now...
Well, I don't suppose it could hurt to tell you, <FirstName>. After all, you did come through for me back in Ghaarak...

This chest of gold is my earnings from my service to the ShadowGuard, <FirstName>. Five years of service, and I have finally collect enough gold to make my payment... a payment that may yet save my life...

You see, before I came to be one of the ShadowGuard, I once was one of the most feared mercenaries of the outlaw city of Laceri. Well, "feared" may be a bit too strong... more along the lines of useful...
But even more than my valuable skills in subterfuge, I was known as the best card player for a hundred leagues of the city. None could beat Tarin Lightfingers in a game of cards!
<StartAction>[Tarin's expression darkens a bit.]</Start> Then came that fateful day... I made the mistake of joining a card game at the tables of Pharos Nightcrawler, infamous crime lord of Laceri...
To this day, I still believe Pharos rigged the game, for I was positive I had the winning hand of cards in our last round. Alas, such was not to be, and I lost a sizeable debt to the crime lord...

Unfortunately, I could not pay the amount I owed to him, and I took to hiding as Pharos Nightcrawler sent his assassins against me. Many are the tales of my great exploits in this time, and I, little Tarin, escaped them all!

It was only a matter of time before even my luck ran out, however, and Pharos had become obsessed with tracking me down. That was when I met Overlord Vhorkas, and he offered me protection against my pursuers...

So, I came to be among the ShadowGuard, and thought I had escaped Pharos Nightcrawler's shadow once and for all. But, encountering his men in Ghaarak changed all that for me, and now I know I'll never truly be safe.
So, I have gathered all the gold I've saved over the years here, and I plan to pay this debt off once and for all. Even a crook like Pharos will have to respect a Halfling whose paid his debt...
Indeed it is, my <lad/lass>, indeed it is. If truth be told, I'll be quite pleased once this cursed debt is lifted off my head...
Soon enough, I'll go to settle the debt, but that journey lies yet ahead of me.
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 1. >>
Thank you so much for saving my life, <FirstName>. I don't know how I could ever repay you for your kind act.
Well, er, as you wish, <CUSTOM6004>. I certainly don't want to trouble you any further after all you've done for me... Still, I would like to give you something for your efforts...
Yes, yes, I suppose you're right. Pharos Nightcrawler's lackeys may still be wandering around here, and it would do little good for them to catch sight of me...
I'd like to offer you the 400 gold I won here in Ghaarak, as payment for my brave rescue. It's the least I can give...

<StartAction>[Grumble.]</Start> I suppose I could part with a bit extra... though now I won't be taking anything home with me... Still, without your help, it wouldn't make much difference, so here's 500 gold for your help.
Well, I ought to be off on my way now. No good staying around here much longer. Good luck to you, <FirstName>, and I have a feeling we may yet see each other before all is over and done with!
<StartAction>[The little Halfling makes his way towards the Docks, in preparation to leave Ghaarak for safety.]</Start>

I'll do my best, <CUSTOM6004>, but that's a lot to ask out of ol' Tarin Lightfingers! After all, card playing is my specialty! Still, though, it's kind of you not to rob me of my earnings, and thank you once more.
Shall we make our way out of this foul place, <FirstName>?
I suppose I can, but please be quick! I don't much care to stay down here any longer than necessary...
<StartAction>[Tarin turns his groggy eyes towards you, shaking his head to clear the fog.]</Start> Ugh... my poor little head...
Thank the gods you're here, <FirstName>! I thought I would end my days in the dungeons of Pharos Nightcrawler for sure this time!
<StartAction>[Tarin appears a bit downcast, but nods in agreement.]</Start> As you would have it, <FirstName>. I'll wait here til you say it's safe to do otherwise.
<StartAction>[Tarin nods.]</Start> Sounds like a decent enough plan to me...
Lead the way, <FirstName>!
<StartAction>[Tarin turns to Lyen.]</Start> Can you go out ahead and get our ship ready? We should prepare our escape immediately if we're to get out of here in one piece...
<StartAction>[Lyen nods and quickly darts into the shadows.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Tarin looks a bit embarrassed.]</Start> Well, yes, in a fashion. You see, this chap in Laceri, a nasty fellow who goes by Pharos Nightcrawler, seems to want my head upon a spike...

It's all over a bunch of foolishness, but he seems quite adamant in his pursuit of me. But that's a long story, and I'd say we have far greater worries at the moment... as in how I'm going to get out of here...
<StartAction>[Tarin notices your uniform, and his eyes grow wide in terror.]</Start> Oh no! So... so you've come for me then...
<StartAction>[As his vision clears, though, Tarin realizes who you are, and a great smile breaks out over his face.]</Start> Why you sneaky rascal! That's quite the disguise you have there!
If you'd like to join us for a card game, <FirstName>, speak with this Malthar gent. I'm sure he'll fill you in on the details...

<StartAction>[The tall, dark skinned man bows before Tarin, a rather strange sight, as the man stands nearly twice as high as the small Halfling.]</Start> Good day to you, sir Halfling. I am Malthar, and I wish to extend my greetings to you.
Nice to meet ya', Malthar. I am Tarin Lightfingers, traveller of the Northern Reaches and card player extraordinaire! Pleased to meet your acquaintance!
The same to you, small sir. My companions and I are seeking a bit of company to pass the time with, perhaps play a few hands of cards... Would you be interested in joining us?
A game of cards, eh? Can't say I'd be willing to pass that up, and there isn't much else going on at the moment... Sure, why not?
Excellent! <StartAction>[Malthar looks towards you and Lyen.]</Start> Your companions are welcome to come along, if they like. Come, follow me!
I'd love for you to come join us, <FirstName>. If you feel up for a bit of fun, why don't you come join us?
While I would prefer just as well that you didn't join us, <FirstName>, I suppose the invitation is open to you as well. Do as you like...
Come along, Lyen! We have yet more gold to win before the <quarterday> is done!
<StartAction>[Lyen smiles and shakes his head at the Halfling's insistence on gambling, but follows suit anyway.]</Start>
Come along, my friends. The <quarterday> is still young! <StartAction>[This Malthar fellow motions for Tarin and  Lyen to follow, and you suppose you could tag along if you like.]</Start>
I can see the glowing expression of Ghan even from here, <FirstName>, so I would assume the Soul Brooch is once more in his possession...
It is quite noble of you to aid Ghan without any sort of reward, <FirstName>. You're a good <CUSTOM6004>, and I thank you for all you have done.
As promised, I shall pay you your reward. <StartAction>[Tarin counts out the agreed amount from his purse.]</Start>
You've earned my respect this day, <FirstName>, and I will not forget your help. Who knows? Perhaps we will find our paths cross once more...
Now, the <quarterday> is still young, and I... <StartAction>[Tarin is cut off mid sentence as a slim, wiry man approaches...]</Start>
Even from here, I can tell Ghan's expression is still quite glum... Did he not accept the offering of the Soul Brooch?
You are truly a despicable person, <FirstName>, refusing Ghan his Soul Brooch simply to weighten your own purse! I want no more to do with you, <CUSTOM6004>!
<StartAction>[Tarin rubs his chin in deep thought.]</Start> Perhaps I can yet find a way to return it to him, in a fashion that will allow Ghan to accept it without going against this honor of his...
Will you give me the Soul Brooch, <FirstName>? I believe, given a bit of time, I can find a suitable way to return it to Ghan...
<StartAction>[Tarin frowns as he notices you do not possess the Soul Brooch anymore.]</Start> Well, you'll have to retrieve it first, <FirstName>. I'll wait for your return here...
I'm glad to see that you still honor your promise, <FirstName>. <StartAction>[Tarin holds out his hand to accept the Soul Brooch.]</Start>
I'd still like to pay you the reward I promised, but you will have to give me the Soul Brooch first...
You are truly a despicable person, <FirstName>, refusing Ghan his Soul Brooch simply to weighten your own purse! I want no more to do with you, <CUSTOM6004>!
Have you brought the Soul Brooch with you, <FirstName>?
<StartAction>[Sigh.]</Start> Very well then, <lad/lass>. Please do hurry, though, for I truly hate to see Ghan so miserable over this affair.
Why... why you... you greedy little dog! Get out of my sight! I may not be called a rogue for nothing, but you, <sir/madam>, are nothing short of a petty villian!
Ah, excellent! Here's what I would like you to do. Take the brooch back to Ghan, and tell him you won it in a card game.
From what I hear of Minotaur culture, if the brooch has been recovered in the same manner it was lost, in this case through a game of chance, then it does not bring dishonor to the Minotaur.
Good. Once it's in his hands, return to me here for your reward. Now, on your way, <CUSTOM6004>... <StartAction>[Tarin motions towards Ghan, still sulking in the corner of the tavern.]</Start>

Poor Ghan... I feel truly terrible about his predicament. That Mylok fellow is known for rigging his card games to benefit his own purse, and I fear Ghan may have fallen prey to one of Mylok's scams...
No, I suppose you wouldn't care about anyone but yourself, now would you, <FirstName>? He's nothing more than a stupid Minotaur, right? How's he going to get back his brooch without our aid?

Well, perhaps that's true, and perhaps it's not. Knowing Mylok, he likely had this whole scenario planned before he ever played against Ghan. Say what you want about us gamblers, but it doesn't make foul play any better...
You'd be willing to help out a fellow down on his luck like that? I've got to say I'm impressed, <FirstName>. There's not many in this city that would offer to do such a thing.
As you wish, <FirstName>... <StartAction>[Tarin gives you a slightly disapproving look, but shrugs and lets the matter drop.]</Start> See you around, <CUSTOM6004>...
A mercenary to the core, eh? Well, I suppose we do all have our needs for wealth. I tell you what, if you can get this Soul Brooch back from Mylok, I'd be willing to reward you with 100 gold pieces.
Perhaps you and I are of a kindred spirit, <FirstName>. I tell you what. If you can get back this Soul Brooch from Mylok, I'd be willing to give you 100 gold pieces for it.
And they call me a rogue! Very well, if you insist on breaking my purse, I suppose I can go a bit higher... 200 gold pieces it is.

Good to hear! You can likely find that scumbag, Mylok, creeping around here in the Market District. Find him, and see if you can get back that Soul Brooch. Return to me with it, and we'll arrange for it to be returned to Ghan.
Well, that is quite noble of you! It's good to see that some are swayed for higher purposes than gold...

<StartAction>[Tarin seems a bit anxious as the roaring Minotaur hovers over the ruins of the card table, and rightly so, for the Minotaur looms as a giant over the Halfling's small frame.]</Start> Easy now, Ghan...
<StartAction>[Lyen, having drawn a blade, directs his weapon threateningly towards the Minotaur.]</Start> Keep your hands off him, Ghan...

<StartAction>[Slowly, the Minotaur seems to gather his calm, and the fire in his eyes dies down.]</Start> I... I apologize. You... you won fairly... and... and I shall honor the rules. It's just... I just needed the gold...
<StartAction>[The large Minotaur hangs his head in shame.]</Start> I shall never regain my honor now! I shall have to return to Charach and tell my Vhaarah that I lost our Soul Brooch...
Easy now, big fellow. We are all friends here, and I certainly didn't mean for a simple game of fun to turn into this. Why don't you tell us what happened, and perhaps we can help...

<StartAction>[Ghan turns his gaze towards the little Halfling.]</Start> Two nights ago, I lost a game of cards to Mylok, a dirty little man here in the Market. I... I had no gold to pay my debt, and was forced to give him my Soul Brooch.

Among my people, there can be no greater shame than losing one's Soul Brooch. It is a symbol of the life bond between myself and my love, Vhaarah. To lose such a great gift shows dishonor and weakness.
If it means that much to you, Ghan, I can give you the gold to buy back your Soul Brooch. I was only playing for fun anyway, and it would be little trouble to give you the gold you need...

That is kind of you to offer, Tarin Lightfingers, but I cannot accept such aid. It is I who brought this upon myself, and it is I who must face the consequences of my action. To accept your gift would only increase my shame...
<StartAction>[With head bowed low, the Minotaur slowly walks away from the table, his massive shoulders slumped in despair...]</Start>

<StartAction>[The diminutive Halfling, playing a card game with a Minotaur and a Ranger, jumps a bit when you tap him on the shoulder, but recovers quickly from his startle and gives you a wide grin.]</Start>

Greetings to you, <sir/madam>! I am Tarin Lightfingers, Halfling card player extraordinaire! These two large gentlemen are Lyen Silverblade, my close personal friend, and Ghan, a Minotaur from the Isle of Charach.
As you wish. Should you find you wish a bit of friendly company at a later time, do feel free to come back and chat with me for a while.
<StartAction>[In a blink of the eye, the Halfling has returned once more to playing his card game, oblivious to your presence.]</Start>
Well then, we are in most esteemed company! I hear your father has become a bit of a local legend around these parts, bringing the city of Ghaarak under Imperial rule and all.

Well, you sure seem to be in a bad mood... Perhaps you should take a load off and join us for a card game. We would love to have such an honored guest at our tables, and perhaps it will lighten your spirits a bit.
Well, it certainly is a pleasure to meet you, <FirstName>. Would you care to join us for a game of cards? We would be quite honored to have such a well-mannered young <man/woman> join us for a bit.
Do as you like, my young friend. <StartAction>[Tarin motions to an empty seat beside him, and turns back to his cards.]</Start>

<StartAction>[After a few minutes of playing redhead, Tarin manages to beat his two larger opponents, collecting the sizeable bet which has grown on the table.]</Start> Sorry, gentlemen, but it seems I have outwitted you yet again!
Excellent to hear, <FirstName>! Make yourself at ease among your new friends! <StartAction>[Tarin motions for you to take a seat beside him at the table.]</Start>

<StartAction>[Tarin shuffles the deck of cards in a rapid, impressive display.]</Start> The name of the game is redhead, <FirstName>. We've been playing for a while, but I can go over the rules if you need me to.
Here's how redhead works. We'll start off the game by placing the ante of 5 gold pieces. I deal two cards to each player, one which is laid down, the other which is facing up for all to see.
After the initial bet, I deal out another round of cards to players who ask for it, and you have to place 5 more gold pieces to stay in. This continues until every player has had their turn.

The goal is to have a total number of cards whose sum is less than or equal to 21. The player with the highest score without exceeding 21 wins. If two hands are tied, the player with the most number of cards wins. Got it?
Everyone whose going to play, pay up 5 gold pieces.
Now I'll pass out the cards... <StartAction>[You are dealt a <CUSTOM7000> and a <CUSTOM7001>.]</Start>
<StartAction>[The ranger grunts in acknowledgement that he will stay in the game. His visible card is a 10.]</Start>
<StartAction>[The Minotaur seems to be a bit nervous, but he agrees to play this hand. He is dealt his cards, his visible card coming up a 3.]</Start>
I'll stay in as well. <StartAction>[The Halfling deals out his two cards, his visible card a <CUSTOM7011>.]</Start>

<StartAction>[The cards now showing are:
Your Hand: <CUSTOM7000><CUSTOM7001><CUSTOM7002><CUSTOM7003><CUSTOM7004> : Total <CUSTOM7009>
Tarin's Visible Cards: <CUSTOM7011><CUSTOM7012><CUSTOM7013> 
Lyen's Visible Cards: 10
Ghan's Visible Cards: 3]</Start>
If you want to stay in, you have to place another 5 gold pieces into the bet. If you do so, you can either accept a card or hold your hand as is. Otherwise you can admit defeat and fold.

Looks like everyone is still in! <StartAction>[Lyen accepts a card, bringing his visible total to 19. Ghan passes on a card for this hand.]</Start> <FirstName>, what shall it be? Do you want another card?
<StartAction>[Tarin deals you a <CUSTOM7002>, bringing your total to <CUSTOM7009>.]</Start>
I think I'll hold on this hand...
I'll take a card as well... <StartAction>[Tarin deals himself a <CUSTOM7012>, bringing his total visible cards to <CUSTOM7019>.]</Start>

<StartAction>[The cards now showing are:
Your Hand: <CUSTOM7000><CUSTOM7001><CUSTOM7002><CUSTOM7003><CUSTOM7004> : Total <CUSTOM7009>
Tarin's Visible Cards: <CUSTOM7011><CUSTOM7012><CUSTOM7013>
Lyen's Visible Cards: 10 9
Ghan's Visible Cards: 3]</Start>

Now for the last round of cards. If you want to stay in, you have to place another 5 gold pieces into the bet. If you do so, you can either accept a card or hold your hand as is. Otherwise admit defeat and fold.
<StartAction>[Everyone else throws in as well.]</Start> Now, now, we have ourselves an interesting game, my friends! Who wants a last card, and who will hold?
Give me another, Halfling...
<StartAction>[Tarin cocks his eyebrow at the darkly dressed man sitting next to him.]</Start> You sure about that, Lyen? You have 19 showing...
You'll not fool me this game, little fellow! Give me a card! <StartAction>[Tarin shrugs, dealing out a 9 to the roguish man, bringing his visible total to 28.]</Start>
Sorry, big guy, but looks like you're out of this game...
<StartAction>[Lyen tosses down his hand and leans back in his chair, shaking his head.]</Start> I hate card games.
<StartAction>[Ghan motions that he would like to have a card dealt to him. Tarin obliges, dealing Ghan a 1, bringing the Minotaur's visible total to 4.]</Start>
How 'bout it, <FirstName>? Do you want another card, or will you pass on this deal?
<StartAction>[Tarin deals you a <CUSTOM7003>, bringing your total to <CUSTOM7009>.]</Start>
I think I'll hold on this hand...
I'll take a card as well... <StartAction>[Tarin deals himself a <CUSTOM7013>, bringing his total visible cards to <CUSTOM7019>.]</Start>
Let's see what everyone has... <StartAction>[Tarin motions for the remaining players to lay down their hands.]</Start>

<StartAction>[The cards now showing are:
Your Hand: <CUSTOM7000><CUSTOM7001><CUSTOM7002><CUSTOM7003><CUSTOM7004> : Total <CUSTOM7009>
Tarin's Hand: <CUSTOM7010><CUSTOM7011><CUSTOM7012><CUSTOM7013> : Total <CUSTOM7019>
Ghan's Hand: 1 4 1: Total 5]</Start>
Sorry, my friends, but looks like ol' Tarin has won again! <StartAction>[Tarin grins widely as he gathers the large pile of gold coins to him.]</Start>
Looks like you're the winner, <FirstName>! Congratulations on a job well done! <StartAction>[Tarin slides the pile of gold coins across the table to you.]</Start>

<StartAction>[Suddenly, you notice the large Minotaur, Ghan, flare his eyes wide.]</Start> The fates curse you, curse you all! <StartAction>[With a mighty swing of his fist, Ghan demolishes the table before him, sending cards flying everywhere.]</Start>
Really? He said that? Well, if that's what he chooses to consider me, consider me honored.

Comment.value: Default dialogue when the henchman is a member of the player's party.

value.0: What can ol' Tarin Lightfingers do for you, <CUSTOM6004>?
I think we're safe enough here.
Very well.
What part of my inventory would you like to manage, <FirstName>?

Comment.value: Default dialogue when the henchman is a member of the player's party.

value.0: What do you wish of me, <FirstName>?
As you wish, <FirstName>. I hope that we may continue to work with one another at a later time, but for now I bid you farewell.
Should you decide that you do indeed need my aid, I will be in the Imperial District. Seek me out there should you feel you need my assistance.
My services are at your command, <FirstName>.
Very well, <FirstName>.
Very well, <FirstName>.
I will try to heal you even if I am being attacked at close range.
Very well, I will heal you only if I am not in hand-to-hand combat.
As you wish.
I hope this is a wise decision, as I am far more skilled on the front lines of battle, but I shall do as you command.
I can do that. When the combat begins I'll rush in and use melee weapons.
Of course. When the combat begins I'll stay back and attack with my ranged weapons from a distance. I'll switch weapons if the enemies get too close.
Sure. What would you like me to do?
Very well. I will avoid melee combat unless I am cornered.
I like your style, <FirstName>. I didn't know you had such a streak within you, but I must say I am impressed.
That may be hard to judge, but I shall do my best.
Very well, I'll wait until the last possible moment!
Very well. I will do what I feel is best.

Varhun's death should signal an end to the threat against you and your father, but it might be wise for us to go to Magistrate Okaris now. My suggestion would be to head to the Imperial Estate, but do as you wish.
It appears Varhun has bested us, <FirstName>. I fear we can do little more against him, for the evidence has been destroyed. We will simply have to hope that luck remains with you and your father...
I believe we have Varhun now. It should only be a matter of confronting the Chancellor at this point. Come, let us put an end to this...
I believe you were wise to enlist the aid of Captain Anagril. He seems to be a decent man. Let us see what we can uncover in Varhun's chambers.
I'm not so sure that confronting Varhun was the wisest decision... He may now have time to rid himself of any evidence. We can only hope that we still find some proof of his guilt.

I have to admit I am quite surprised to learn that a high ranking Imperial official such as Chancellor Varhun would be involved in a matter like this. I believe we are going to have to confront the Chancellor on this issue.
I suppose bloodshed was inevitable, considering the fact Mikel desired your death. Let's see if Mikel's chamber holds any information regarding his motives for plotting against you and your father.
We've gotten this far without bloodshed, so perhaps we can yet avoid bloodshed. Why not speak with Mikel, and see what he has to say about the assassination attempt?
You did well in securing aid from Officer Ganolin. We should have an easier time of confronting Mikel Ravenclaw now. Let's head toward Ravenclaw Tavern...
We need to find some way of discovering Mikel's motives behind plotting against you and your father. We will have to be careful entering his chambers, though, for he keeps himself well guarded.
Which item would you like me to unequip?
Very well, <FirstName>. I have unequipped all my items.
As you wish, <FirstName>. I have successfully unequipped <CUSTOM10001>.
I am sorry, <FirstName>, but I do not have an item in that inventory slot.
